<item>
            <title>[SUREFIRE-1217] Differentiate XML schema for failsafe and surefire</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-1217</link>
                <project id="12317927" key="SUREFIRE">Maven Surefire (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The XML schema introduced in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-964&quot; title=&quot;TEST-*.xml files generated by Surefire throw validation warnings in Eclipse for no grammer constraints (DTD or XML schema) referenced in the document&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SUREFIRE-964&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SUREFIRE-964&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; does not differentiate between surefire and failsafe. Currently they are not different, but in the future they might be.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tibor17&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tibor17&quot;&gt;tibor17&lt;/a&gt; suggested to adapt &lt;tt&gt;StatelessXmlReporter&lt;/tt&gt; in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-1216&quot; title=&quot;TEST-*.xml files generated by Surefire are invalid&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SUREFIRE-1216&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SUREFIRE-1216&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
